<!--
Purpose: Template for creating standardized markdown file headers
Scope: All markdown documentation files (.md) in any project
Overview: This template provides the standard header structure for markdown documentation files.
    When used, it generates a complete file header with all mandatory and recommended fields following
    the atemporal documentation principle. The generated header includes project-specific information
    and helps readers quickly understand the document's purpose, scope, and content without reading
    the entire file. Use this template as the starting point for all new markdown documentation.

Placeholders:
  {{DOCUMENT_TITLE}}: Document title (should match filename without extension)
    - Type: string
    - Example: "API Documentation Standards" or "User Guide"
    - Required: yes

  {{PURPOSE}}: Brief description of what this document covers (1-2 lines)
    - Type: string
    - Example: "Complete guide for implementing user authentication in the application"
    - Required: yes

  {{SCOPE}}: What areas/components this document applies to
    - Type: string
    - Example: "All authentication flows including registration, login, and OAuth2 integration"
    - Required: yes

  {{OVERVIEW}}: Comprehensive explanation of document content (3-5+ lines)
    - Type: string (multiline)
    - Example: "This guide covers the complete user authentication system including password-based authentication, JWT token management, refresh token handling, and OAuth2 integration..."
    - Required: yes

  {{DEPENDENCIES}}: Related documents, external resources, or prerequisite knowledge
    - Type: string
    - Example: "User service API documentation, JWT library documentation, OAuth2 provider setup guides"
    - Required: no
    - Default: Can be omitted if no dependencies

  {{EXPORTS}}: Key information, standards, procedures, or guidelines this document provides
    - Type: string
    - Example: "Authentication implementation patterns, security best practices, integration examples"
    - Required: no
    - Default: Can be omitted if not applicable

  {{RELATED}}: Links to related documentation, external resources, or cross-references
    - Type: string
    - Example: "API documentation for auth endpoints, user service documentation, security standards"
    - Required: no
    - Default: Can be omitted if no related docs

  {{IMPLEMENTATION}}: Notable documentation patterns, structures, or organizational approaches
    - Type: string
    - Example: "JWT-based authentication with RSA signing, OAuth2 authorization code flow"
    - Required: no
    - Default: Can be omitted if not applicable

Usage:
  1. Copy template to destination:
     cp .ai/templates/file-header-markdown.template path/to/your-document.md

  2. Replace all placeholders with actual values:
     - {{DOCUMENT_TITLE}}: Replace with actual document title
     - {{PURPOSE}}: Replace with brief description (1-2 lines)
     - {{SCOPE}}: Replace with coverage area
     - {{OVERVIEW}}: Replace with comprehensive explanation (3-5+ lines)
     - {{DEPENDENCIES}}: Replace or remove if not needed
     - {{EXPORTS}}: Replace or remove if not needed
     - {{RELATED}}: Replace or remove if not needed
     - {{IMPLEMENTATION}}: Replace or remove if not needed

  3. Remove this template header (lines 1-XX)

  4. Verify document:
     - Check all placeholders are replaced
     - Ensure no {{}} remain
     - Verify mandatory fields present (Purpose, Scope, Overview)
     - Check for atemporal language (no "currently", "now", "recently")

  5. Validate markdown (optional):
     markdownlint path/to/your-document.md

Related: FILE_HEADER_STANDARDS.md, how-to-write-file-headers.md
-->

---
file: {{FILE_PATH}}
purpose: {{PURPOSE}}
audience: {{AUDIENCE}}
status: {{STATUS}}
updated: {{UPDATED}}
exports: {{EXPORTS}}
related: {{RELATED}}
overview: {{OVERVIEW}}
---

